      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Howard Elliott, president of the\nNorthern Pacific, will be in and\naround Spokane for several days.\nHe is against insisting on terminal\nrates in the franchises of the North\nCoast and Milwaukee, and says\nthat it can not be done. He sug-\ngests that the fight before the In\nterstate Commerce Commission be\ncontinued.\n\n\nHe conveys a little bad news for\nhis would-be competing lines, how\never, by saying that they can not\nenter Spokane over the Hill roads\nand that the others are too busy\nto care for them. That if the new\nroads are to come in it must be\nover their own lines."
    }
  ]
